## Statefullness In streamLit

Statefulness in Streamlit is one of the most important concepts to understand because Streamlit apps are rerun from top to bottom every time the user interacts with them.

1. What does "state" mean?

State is data that persists across reruns of your app.

Examples:

User's name entered in a text box
Counter value
Login status
Selected options
Uploaded file
Model predictions already computed
Without state, these values would be lost whenever Streamlit reruns the script.
Multiple users
Each user gets their own session state.
If User A sets:
st.session_state.count = 5
User B still sees:
count = 0
Session state is per user session, not global.

Entry Purpose
.env Stores environment variables and secrets
.vscode/ VS Code editor settings
\*.pyc Compiled Python bytecode files
.DS_Store macOS system metadata file
**pycache**/ Folder containing Python bytecode cache
venv/ Python virtual environment
.streamlit/ Streamlit configuration files
